◆ dsa_change_setpoint_a()

int dsa_change_setpoint_a ( DSA_DRIVE_BASE *  grp,
int  sidx,
dword  flags,
DSA_HANDLER  handler,
void *  param 
)

Change current setpoint (Command:STA) - asynchronous.

The function will copy the "sidx" depth in the depth 0 of parameter specified by "flags". This will start a move.

Deprecated:
since EDI-4.24A. Use dsa_new_setpoint_a instead.
Parameters
grpa pointer to the group structure
sidxthe buffer index
flagsthe OR-value of the following flags
  • DSA_STA_POS get the KL210 specified depth as position for the next move
  • DSA_STA_SPD get the KL211 specified depth as speed for the next move
  • DSA_STA_ACC get the KL212 specified depth as acceleration for the next move
  • DSA_STA_JRK get the K213 specified depth as jerk for the next move
  • DSA_STA_PROFILE_TYPE get the K202 specified depth as profile type for the next move
  • DSA_STA_LKT_NUMBER_AND_MODE get the K203 and K207 specified depth as look-up table number and look-up table mode for the next move
  • DSA_STA_LKT_TIME get the K204 specified depth as look-up table time for the next move
  • DSA_STA_LKT_AMPLITUDE get the KL208 specified depth as look-up table amplitude for the next move
  • DSA_STA_ROTARY_MVT_TYPE get the K209 specified depth as rotary movement type for the next move
  • DSA_STA_CALCULATED_MVT_PROFILE get the K230 specified depth as calculated movement profile for the next move
  • DSA_STA_CALCULATED_MVT_TIME get the K229 specified depth as calculated movement time for the next move
handlerthe handler function called when the function is executed
paramuser parameter transmitted to the handler function
Returns
a negative value if an error or a timeout has occurred
DSA_EACQDEVINUSE One of the device is already doing an acquisition
DSA_EACQNOTPOSSIBLE Drives must be connected with transnet
DSA_EAXESRECOVER Transnet established but axes not recovered
DSA_EBADCOMPRESSTOOL Unhandled compress tool
DSA_EBADDRIVER bad device driver installed
DSA_EBADDRVVER bad drive version
DSA_EBADIPOLGRP bad ipol group
DSA_EBADLIBRARY function of external library not found
DSA_EBADPARAM bad parameter
DSA_EBADSEQVERSION Version syntax error (Syntax: [n]n.nnc)
DSA_EBADSTATE bad state
DSA_EBUSERROR bus in error state
DSA_EBUSRESET bus in reset state
DSA_ECANCEL transaction canceled
DSA_ECFGCOMPFILE File compiled for different axes configuration
DSA_ECONVERT conversion error
DSA_EDRVERROR drive in error
DSA_EDRVFAILED drive failed
DSA_EEQUATION Equation cannot be resolved
DSA_EFLUSH Flush communication timeout
DSA_EINTERNAL internal error
DSA_EMAPNOTACTIVATED Mapping cannot be activated by the device
DSA_EMETAHEADER bad metadata header
DSA_EMETAHEADERVER bad metadata header version
DSA_EMETAPARSER Metadata parsing error
DSA_ENOACK no acknowledge
DSA_ENODRIVE no drive response
DSA_ENOFREESLOT no free slot available
DSA_ENOFWINPOOL Firmware not found in FW pool
DSA_ENOLIBRARY external library not found
DSA_ENOTIMPLEMENTED not implemented
DSA_EOBSOLETE function is obsolete
DSA_EOPENPORT open com error
DSA_ERTVREADSYNCRO RTV read synchronization error
DSA_ERTVWRITESYNCRO RTV write syncronisation error
DSA_ESYNTAX Mapping file syntax error
DSA_ESYSTEM system error
DSA_ETIMEOUT timeout error
DSA_ETRANS transaction error
DSA_ETRANSNET Transnet is not established in imparted time
DSA_EUNZIP Unable to unzip metadata buffer
DSA_EUPLOADFILE MD5 of uploaded file does not fit MD5 of original
DSA_EWFP Communication not opened(device in WaitForProgram)

◆ dsa_change_setpoint_s()

int dsa_change_setpoint_s ( DSA_DRIVE_BASE *  grp,
int  sidx,
dword  flags,
long  timeout 
)

Change current setpoint (Command:STA) - synchronous.

The function will copy the "sidx" depth in the depth 0 of parameter specified by "flags". This will start a move.

Deprecated:
since EDI-4.24A. Use dsa_new_setpoint_s instead.
Parameters
grpa pointer to the group structure
sidxthe buffer index
flagsthe OR-value of the following flags
  • DSA_STA_POS get the KL210 specified depth as position for the next move
  • DSA_STA_SPD get the KL211 specified depth as speed for the next move
  • DSA_STA_ACC get the KL212 specified depth as acceleration for the next move
  • DSA_STA_JRK get the K213 specified depth as jerk for the next move
  • DSA_STA_PROFILE_TYPE get the K202 specified depth as profile type for the next move
  • DSA_STA_LKT_NUMBER_AND_MODE get the K203 and K207 specified depth as look-up table number and look-up table mode for the next move
  • DSA_STA_LKT_TIME get the K204 specified depth as look-up table time for the next move
  • DSA_STA_LKT_AMPLITUDE get the KL208 specified depth as look-up table amplitude for the next move
  • DSA_STA_ROTARY_MVT_TYPE get the K209 specified depth as rotary movement type for the next move
  • DSA_STA_CALCULATED_MVT_PROFILE get the K230 specified depth as calculated movement profile for the next move
  • DSA_STA_CALCULATED_MVT_TIME get the K229 specified depth as calculated movement time for the next move
timeoutthe timeout value in ms or
  • DSA_DEF_TIMEOUT a value depending of the used communication bus (generally 1 or 2 seconds)
  • INFINITE infinite timeout

)

Parameters
objthe drive pointer

kindthe kind of value to read
  • DSA_GET_CURRENT get current value, bypass pending commands
  • DSA_GET_MIN_VALUE get the minimum value
  • DSA_GET_MAX_VALUE get the maximum value
  • DSA_GET_DEF_VALUE get the default value
timeoutthe timeout value in ms or
  • DSA_DEF_TIMEOUT a value depending of the used communication bus (generally 1 or 2 seconds)
  • INFINITE infinite timeout

◆ dsa_new_setpoint_a()

int dsa_new_setpoint_a ( DSA_DRIVE_BASE *  grp,
int  sidx,
dword  flags,
DSA_HANDLER  handler,
void *  param 
)

Define a new setpoint (Command:STA) - asynchronous.

The function will copy the "sidx" depth in the depth 0 of parameter specified by "flags". This will start a move

Parameters
grpa pointer to the group structure
sidxthe buffer index
flagsthe OR-value of the following flags
  • DSA_STA_POS get the KL210 specified depth as position for the next move
  • DSA_STA_SPD get the KL211 specified depth as speed for the next move
  • DSA_STA_ACC get the KL212 specified depth as acceleration for the next move
  • DSA_STA_JRK get the K213 specified depth as jerk for the next move
  • DSA_STA_PROFILE_TYPE get the K202 specified depth as profile type for the next move
  • DSA_STA_LKT_NUMBER_AND_MODE get the K203 and K207 specified depth as look-up table number and look-up table mode for the next move
  • DSA_STA_LKT_TIME get the K204 specified depth as look-up table time for the next move
  • DSA_STA_LKT_AMPLITUDE get the KL208 specified depth as look-up table amplitude for the next move
  • DSA_STA_ROTARY_MVT_TYPE get the K209 specified depth as rotary movement type for the next move
  • DSA_STA_CALCULATED_MVT_PROFILE get the K230 specified depth as calculated movement profile for the next move
  • DSA_STA_CALCULATED_MVT_TIME get the K229 specified depth as calculated movement time for the next move
handlerthe handler function called when the function is executed
paramuser parameter transmitted to the handler function
Returns
a negative value if an error or a timeout has occurred
DSA_EACQDEVINUSE One of the device is already doing an acquisition
DSA_EACQNOTPOSSIBLE Drives must be connected with transnet
DSA_EAXESRECOVER Transnet established but axes not recovered
DSA_EBADCOMPRESSTOOL Unhandled compress tool
DSA_EBADDRIVER bad device driver installed
DSA_EBADDRVVER bad drive version
DSA_EBADIPOLGRP bad ipol group
DSA_EBADLIBRARY function of external library not found
DSA_EBADPARAM bad parameter
DSA_EBADSEQVERSION Version syntax error (Syntax: [n]n.nnc)
DSA_EBADSTATE bad state
DSA_EBUSERROR bus in error state
DSA_EBUSRESET bus in reset state
DSA_ECANCEL transaction canceled
DSA_ECFGCOMPFILE File compiled for different axes configuration
DSA_ECONVERT conversion error
DSA_EDRVERROR drive in error
DSA_EDRVFAILED drive failed
DSA_EEQUATION Equation cannot be resolved
DSA_EFLUSH Flush communication timeout
DSA_EINTERNAL internal error
DSA_EMAPNOTACTIVATED Mapping cannot be activated by the device
DSA_EMETAHEADER bad metadata header
DSA_EMETAHEADERVER bad metadata header version
DSA_EMETAPARSER Metadata parsing error
DSA_ENOACK no acknowledge
DSA_ENODRIVE no drive response
DSA_ENOFREESLOT no free slot available

◆ dsa_quick_stop_a()

int dsa_quick_stop_a ( DSA_DRIVE_BASE *  grp,
int  mode,
dword  flags,
DSA_HANDLER  handler,
void *  param 
)

Quick stop the drive (Command:HLT/STP/HLO/PWR/HLB/BRK) - asynchronous.

Parameters
grpa pointer to the group structure
modeone of the following options
  • DSA_QS_INFINITE_DEC stop motor with infinite deceleration (depending on flags: HLT, !HLT, STP, from firmware 2.08 only:!STP)
  • DSA_QS_POWER_OFF switch off power bridge (depending on flags:HLO, !HLO, PWR=0, from firmware 2.08 only:!PWR=0)
  • DSA_QS_PROGRAMMED_DEC stop motor with programmed deceleration (depending on flags:HLB, !HLB, BRK from firmware 2.08 only:!BRK)
flagsone of the following options
  • 0 (STP, PWR=0 or BRK depending on the mode)
  • DSA_QS_BYPASS_AND_STOP_SEQUENCE bypass all pending command and force stopping sequences (!HLT, !HLO or !HLB depending on the mode)
  • DSA_QS_STOP_SEQUENCE stop the sequence (HLT, HLO or HLB depending on the mode)
  • DSA_QS_BYPASS_AND_NO_STOP_SEQUENCE bypass all pending command without stopping the sequence (!STP, !PWR=0, !BRK depending on the mode: need AccurET firmware 2.08 at least)
handlerthe handler function called when the function is executed
paramuser parameter transmitted to the handler function
Returns
a negative value if an error or a timeout has occured

DSA_EACQNOTPOSSIBLE Drives must be connected with transnet

◆ dsa_set_jerk_time_a()

int dsa_set_jerk_time_a ( DSA_DRIVE_BASE *  obj,
int  sidx,
double  tim,
DSA_HANDLER  handler,
void *  param 
)

Set the jerk time (K213) - asynchronous.

Depending of the sidx parameter value, the specified controllers will do different actions.

Parameters
objthe object pointer
sidxthe register depth.
  • 0 : set the jerk time on specified axes for actual move if movement is concatenated or for next move if not concatenated
  • 1..3 : set depth 1..3 of parameter k213 with the jerk time.
    Using function dsa_new_setpoint_a() will then start the move to position,speed, acceleration and jerk contained in specified sidx
timthe jerk time (213) value in s
handlerthe handler function called when the value is set
paramuser parameter transmitted to the handler function
Returns
a negative value if an error or a timeout has occurred
DSA_EACQDEVINUSE One of the device is already doing an acquisition
DSA_EACQNOTPOSSIBLE Drives must be connected with transnet

◆ dsa_set_profile_acceleration_a()

int dsa_set_profile_acceleration_a ( DSA_DRIVE_BASE *  obj,
int  sidx,
double  acc,
DSA_HANDLER  handler,
void *  param 
)

Set the absolute maximal acc/deceleration (KL212) - asynchronous.

Depending of the sidx parameter value, the specified controllers will do different actions.

Parameters
objthe object pointer
sidxthe register depth.
  • 0 : set the acceleration on specified axes for actual move if movement is concatenated or for next move if not concatenated
  • 1..3 : set depth 1..3 of parameter KL212 with the acceleration.
    Using function dsa_new_setpoint_a() will then start the move to position,speed, acceleration and jerk contained in specified sidx
accthe absolute max.acc/deceleration value in m/s2, t/s2
handlerthe handler function called when the value is set
paramuser parameter transmitted to the handler function
Returns
a negative value if an error or a timeout has occurred
DSA_EACQDEVINUSE One of the device is already doing an acquisition
DSA_EACQNOTPOSSIBLE Drives must be connected with transnet
DSA_EAXESRECOVER Transnet established but axes not recovered
DSA_EBADCOMPRESSTOOL Unhandled compress tool
DSA_EBADDRIVER bad device driver installed
DSA_EBADDRVVER bad drive version
DSA_EBADIPOLGRP bad ipol group
DSA_EBADLIBRARY function of external library not found

DSA_EBADSEQVERSION Version syntax error (Syntax: [n]n.nnc)
DSA_EBADSTATE bad state
DSA_EBUSERROR bus in error state
DSA_EBUSRESET bus in reset state
DSA_ECANCEL transaction canceled
DSA_ECFGCOMPFILE File compiled for different axes configuration
DSA_ECONVERT conversion error
DSA_EDRVERROR drive in error
DSA_EDRVFAILED drive failed
DSA_EEQUATION Equation cannot be resolved
DSA_EFLUSH Flush communication timeout
DSA_EINTERNAL internal error
DSA_EMAPNOTACTIVATED Mapping cannot be activated by the device
DSA_EMETAHEADER bad metadata header
DSA_EMETAHEADERVER bad metadata header version
DSA_EMETAPARSER Metadata parsing error
DSA_ENOACK no acknowledge
DSA_ENODRIVE no drive response
DSA_ENOFREESLOT no free slot available
DSA_ENOFWINPOOL Firmware not found in FW pool

◆ dsa_set_profile_velocity_a()

int dsa_set_profile_velocity_a ( DSA_DRIVE_BASE *  obj,
int  sidx,
double  vel,
DSA_HANDLER  handler,
void *  param 
)

Set the absolute maximum speed (KL211) - asynchronous.

Depending of the sidx parameter value, the specified controllers will do different actions.

Parameters
objthe object pointer
sidxthe register depth.
  • 0 : set the speed on specified axes for actual move if movement is concatenated or for next move if not concatenated
  • 1..3 : set depth 1..3 of parameter KL211 with the speed.
    Using function dsa_new_setpoint_a() will then start the move to position,speed, acceleration and jerk contained in specified sidx
velthe absolute maximum speed value in m/s, t/s
handlerthe handler function called when the value is set
paramuser parameter transmitted to the handler function
Returns
a negative value if an error or a timeout has occurred

depththe register depth.

On MISCON, will set matrix lines 1..7 of internal parameters of first logical axis to requested values.
posthe target position value in m, t
speedthe speed value in m, t If the speed is 0, KL211:depth will not be set.
IN THIS CASE, NO ACCELERATION CAN BE SPECIFIED.
accthe acceleration of the movement in m/s2, t/s2.
If the acc is 0, KL212:depth will not be set.

paramuser parameter transmitted to the handler function

◆ dsa_set_target_position_a()

int dsa_set_target_position_a ( DSA_DRIVE_BASE *  obj,
int  sidx,
double  pos,
DSA_HANDLER  handler,
void *  param 
)

Set the target position (KL210:depth) - asynchronous.

  • if sidx is 0, command MVE will be sent, and the drive will start a move.
  • if sidx is different than 0, specified depth of KL210 will be set.
    Used on MISCON, the function will start the first logical axis of MISCON.
    Parameters
    objthe object pointer
    sidxthe register depth. Used on MISCON, this parameter can only be 0.
  • 0 : will immediately start a move on the specified axes
  • 1..3 : will set depth 1..3 of parameter KL210 with the position.
    Using function dsa_new_setpoint_a() will then start the move to position contained in specified sidx
    Parameters
    posthe target position value in m, t
    handlerthe handler function called when the value is set
    paramuser parameter transmitted to the handler function
    Returns
    a negative value if an error or a timeout has occurred
    DSA_EACQDEVINUSE One of the device is already doing an acquisition

◆ dsa_set_target_position_from_register_a()

int dsa_set_target_position_from_register_a ( DSA_DRIVE_BASE *  obj,
int  sidx,
int  reg_typ,
int  reg_idx,
int  reg_sidx,
DSA_HANDLER  handler,
void *  param 
)

Set the target position from a register (KL210:depth) - asynchronous.

  • if sidx is 0, command MVE will be sent, and the drive will start a move.
  • if sidx is different than 0, specified depth of KL210 will be set.
    Used on MISCON, the function will start the first logical axis of MISCON.
    Parameters
    objthe object pointer
    sidxthe register depth. Used on MISCON, this parameter can only be 0.
  • 0 : will immediately start a move on the specified axes
  • 1..7 : will set depth 1..7 of parameter KL210 with the position.
    Using function dsa_new_setpoint_s() will then start the move to position, speed, acceleration and jerk contained in specified sidx
    Parameters
    reg_typthe register type which must be used to set the position. Type supported limited to 32/64 bits integer
    reg_idxthe register index which must be used to set the position
    reg_sidxthe register sub-index which must be used to set the position
    handlerthe handler function called when the value is set
    paramuser parameter transmitted to the handler function
    Returns
    a negative value if an error or a timeout has occurred

Start a relative movement (Command:RMVE) - synchronous.

Send a command, specifying relative position.
Speed and acceleration will be the values given in a preceding call to start_profiled_movement or the values of parameters KL211:0 and KL212:0.
Used on MISCON, the function will start the first logical axis of MISCON.

Deprecated:
since EDI-4.24A. Use dsa_start_relative_profiled_movement_ex_s instead.
Parameters
grpthe object containing the device or group of devices
relative_posthe relative position value in m, t
timeoutthe timeout value in ms or
  • DSA_DEF_TIMEOUT a value depending of the used communication bus (generally 1 or 2 seconds)
  • INFINITE infinite timeout
Returns
a negative value if an error or a timeout has occurred
DSA_EACQDEVINUSE One of the device is already doing an acquisition
DSA_EACQNOTPOSSIBLE Drives must be connected with transnet
DSA_EAXESRECOVER Transnet established but axes not recovered
DSA_EBADCOMPRESSTOOL Unhandled compress tool
DSA_EBADDRIVER bad device driver installed
